achievements.title: Early Clinical Exposure
achievements.description:
Learned basic yet important skills including:
°Pulse Measurement
°Blood Pressure Measurement 
°Basic level ECG Interpretation

achievements.title: 95% + Attendance
achievements.description: Every day in class was a step closer to my goals — staying above 95% attendance was my way of proving discipline and determination.

achievements.title: Google Forms & MS Word Webinar
achievements.description: Successfully completed extracurricular courses in MS Word, Google Forms, and MS PowerPoint, gaining practical skills in documentation, data collection, and professional presentations

achievements.title: Theoretical Foundations of Health Research
achievements.description: Attended a series of highly informative lectures on the basics of research in the medical field.

achievements.title: Developing Professionalism and Leadership Skills
achievements.description: My academic journey has always been about more than just knowledge; it's also about building character. This logbook documents my engagement with the "Professionalism" module, which focused on accountability and professional conduct. The sessions honed my skills and understanding of professional behavior in foundational medical subjects and clinical settings.

achievements.title: Basics of Dermatology
achievements.description: Attended a webinar session to understand the basics of Dermatology and the misconceptions. Very useful insight into the field of dermatology.

achievements.title: Struggle Against Dengue
achievements.description: Attended a webinar to gain knowledge about the spread,preventive measures and the treatment of dengue fever.

achievements.title: Stuturing Workshop
achievements.description: Attended a Stuturing Workshop organized by Surgery Interest Group (SIG).It was very fun being taught by resident surgeons at Holy Family Hospital.

achievements.title: Learning how to Deal with Emergency Situations
achievements.description: I attended a very informative webinar session to better understand how to deal with Emergency Situations which is a very important skill especially for a medical student.

reflections.title: Lower Limb Dissection
reflections.content: I dissected the lower limb which despite the difficulty proved to be a terrifying yet fascinating experience.

reflections.title: Learning An Important Skill: How to Administer IM Injections
reflections.content: As a member of Medicos Aid Society, I volunteered for the 2nd Vaccination Camp against Hepatitis where under the guidense of my respected seniors I injected an IM Injection for the first time. I was very nervous but afterwards I felt great amount of happiness upon having learned a practical clinical skill.

reflections.title: Improving My Presentation Skills
reflections.content: I attended a webinar to improve my ability to give presentations. It proved to be a very informative session

reflections.title: Staying Healthy and Fit
reflections.content: Gained knowledge about how to stay healthy and fit in the hectic routine of a medical student. It was a very useful webinar held by MSA-Pakistan.

reflections.title: Taking part and getting 2nd Position in The Trail of Trials
reflections.content: I, along with my Maryam Bukhari,got 2nd position in Trail of Trials; a scavenger hunt especially designed for medical students.

reflections.title: Volunteering for Vaccination Camp and Blood Case Investigations
reflections.content: As an active member of Medicos Aid Society, I have volunteered for the vaccination camp against Hepatitis.I have also done multiple blood case investigations which have given me knowledge about how to deal with people in emergency situations.

personalInfo.title: MBBS RMU 52 Student | Year 1 (Roll no.105)
personalInfo.bio: Passionate medical student dedicated 1. To impart evidence based research oriented medical education. 2. To provide best possible patient care. 3. To inculcate the values of mutual respect and ethical practice of medicine.
